data.title: CITY OF JOPLIN
data.meta_description:
1 review and 9 photos of CITY OF JOPLIN "At the beginning of the race I was Joplin for position. But now I'm just glad to still be in the race.

A very long time ago I had a very good friend in Joplin. He arranged for me to play my first concert in the city and it seems like the whole town showed up. Afterwards I spent part of the night canoodling with a beautiful spectacular girl who I still think about to this day. It was one of those magical nights and I have never forgotten it.

Not long after my visit my friend passed away. It's very confusing and complicated but it was ruled a suicide. It was pretty grisly and horrible. I still have good friends that live here but there is a shadow over the town and my heart ever since.

Then a couple of months later a devastating tornado wiped out a huge portion of the town and caused many casualties.

There will always be a special place in my heart for Joplin and someday I look forward to my return."
